<div style='min-height: 100px;' class='postbody mb-3 mt-4'>Been looking at this one for some time, mustering courage to dive in and I got to say, nice start, even with Generic Villain #1 who is a bully turned up to eleven, the start is quite good. But it is during ch 50+ that I write this, their personalities are all over the place, he is goofy, then he is serious, then he is flirty then he is goofy, then he is serious, then he goes all mature and shit, then he knows ALL that there is to know...Not to mention the girls and their friendship. Consistence was never the strength of this kind mythology, the cultivation mythology I mean, but DAMN, this one got some power levels well established but the characters suddenly got all over the place. I will keep reading, but after this, I am pretty sure the autor change the personalities on a whim to create conflict and drama. And it is funny that the only well developed character is the bully who had consistence and development, even if it is for him to became an even bigger jerk. BUT, I will stay and follow it to the end.<br />
@edit<br />
I take back what I said about the power levels being well established.<br />
@edit2<br />
I am pretty sure that there are 2 authors for this, one is really good and knows how to work the characters personalities, the other enjoys random dramas. The story is good. Quite good, full of ex machina as it is common for its kind, but still good. But the random character looking for drama is beyond normal. It goes like this <button type='button' class='btn btn-sm btn-warning btn-spoiler'>Spoiler</button><p class='spoiler display-none'>&quot;Hey, I know I killed a bunch of people and I am trying to kidnap someone who is probably innocent, but I was nice to you once (ONCE!), so, like, we are totally the best bros ever, right?&quot; &quot;Yeah dude, sure, you killed a bunch of guys, tried to have me killed, but you were nice that one time we talked, so we are like, besties.&quot;</p> Not joking.</div><p class='my-3'><em>Last edited 12 mo <span class='d-none d-xl-inline'>ago</span> by <a style='color: #099; ' id='1' href='/user/1/mangadex'>MangaDex</a>.</em></p><div class='post-btns btn-group btn-group-sm d-flex justify-content-end'><button title='Report' data-item-id='40864' data-type-name='comment' data-type-id='3' type='button' class='report-button btn btn-sm btn-secondary text-warning'><span class='fas fa-flag fa-fw ' aria-hidden='true'></span> <span class='d-none d-md-inline'>Report</span></button></div></td></tr>
